      "message": "So the intent here is that we\u0027ll take this block (i.e. use the transparent index) even if dstInfo is not index8?\n\nIf that fixes your case, I think the bug is a little deeper:\n\nMy thinking is that this color was going to be used as a color (i.e. SkPMColor) if the dstInfo is kN32, and an index if the dstInfo is Index8. If we want a color, we want SK_ColorTRANSPARENT, and if we want an index, we want the index of the transparent pixel (or default to SK_ColorTRANSPARENT if there is not one). Skipping this block means we\u0027ll use the color.\n\nThe fact that this fixes the problem tells me that I was wrong, and we want the index if we\u0027re using a color table (which is always for GIF). Looking at the code for SkSampler::Fill (which is also called by SkSwizzler::fill) though, it looks to me like we\u0027re treating the fill value as a color for a N32 dst (as intended - meaning that SK_ColorTRANSPARENT is what we want), so I must be missing something?",
